nib.text:
A bus driver was wounded by a bullet while driving three children home in Folwell Wednesday afternoon, officials said. 

At around 2:15 p.m., a bus driving was taking children home and going about his route on N. 37th Avenue and Girard Avenue when a bullet went through the windshield. 

The driver was struck in the head and quickly stopped the bus. 

According to a report from [KTSP](https://kstp.com/kstp-news/top-news/bus-driver-shot-in-north-minneapolis-with-3-children-aboard/) police reported that they did not believe the driver's injures were life-threatening. 

All three children, who were under 10-year-old, were taken home by police. 

No arrests were reported. 

Detectives are investigating.
